    "summary": "Mark Waayer brings over 15 year of consulting experience in various industries. \nA combination of social and analytical skills enables him to quickly analyze and understand business issues, align stakeholders and deliver (project) results.\n\nHe is very knowledgeable in the fields of Logistics, Manufacturing, Cost / Value Engineering and IT (ERP/PLM) solutions. As business consultant, he is managing projects and teams that are related to business transformation, product / process performance improvement and IT implementations within various industries.\n \nHe has good communication skills and is capable of quickly getting a good understanding of the business situation and guide the customer towards a solution. \n\nAs a managing consultant, he has been working within an international context for  various customers, for example: Philips, ASML, Bayer, AkzoNobel, Valeo Siemens, VDL, Deutsche Glasfaser, Dutch Ministry of Defense, Ministry of Internal Affairs and Bouwinvest.\nNext to this, he has been responsible for the professional (HR) development of a team within his cluster.\n\nMark holds a master degree in Strategic Management from the RSM Erasmus in Rotterdam and a Bachelors degree in Financial Economic Management.",
